LV analysis

2022-11-07

source("helperFuncs.R")

The data is already regressed for tissue and sex now we also standardize the variance

lvdat=tscaleByGroup(methRegionR, paste(phenoRegion$tissue, phenoRegion$Sex))

run PLIER base function

methres=PLIER::simpleDecomp(lvdat[, ], k=10)

Print differential report

report=LVtissueReport(methres,  phenoRegion[colnames(methres$B),], fdr = 0.05, min.var = 0.01)
print(ggplot()+annotate(geom = 'table', size=4,           x=4, y=0, label=list(data.frame(report[report$p.val<0.05,]  )))+theme_void())

Plot LV results

sigLVs=as.numeric(sub("LV ", "",unique(report$LV)))
pheatmap(cor(t(methres$B[sigLVs,])))

9 and 5 are reundant, we ignore the one with the least variance

boxplot(methres$Z[1:1000,])

sigLVs=setdiff(sigLVs, 5)    
pL=list()
for(i in sigLVs){
  sigTissues=unique(sub(" [FM]", "",report[report$LV==paste("LV",i),]$tissue))
  pL[[paste("LV",i)]]=plotLVtests(methres, phenoRegion, i, tissue = sigTissues)
  
}
ggarrange(plotlist = pL, ncol = 1, common.legend = T)

use rGREAT to evaluate KEGG and GO enrichment based on genomic coverage

tableKEGG=greatEnrichmentLVall(methres,sigLVs, extended_tss = et, gmt = gmtKEGG, min.hits = 20)
tableGO=greatEnrichmentLVall(methres,sigLVs, extended_tss = et, gmt = gmtGO, min.hits = 20)
kable(topNenrichment(tableGO, p.adjust = 0.1, n=5)[, c(1,2,6,7)], row.names = F, digits=5, col.names = c("LV    ", "term", "p_value", "p_adjust") )

goToPlot=as.data.frame(topNenrichment(tableGO, p.adjust = 0.1, n=5))
## [1] "LV 1" "LV 2" "LV 3" "LV 9"
goToPlot$id=sub("\\(.*", "", goToPlot$id)
goToPlot$log10pval=-log10(goToPlot$p_value)
goL=list()
for(lv in unique(goToPlot$LV)){
goL[[lv]]=ggbarplot(goToPlot[goToPlot$LV==lv,], x="id", y="fold_enrichment", fill="log10pval", )+rotateAxes()+coord_flip()+theme_bw(base_size = 8)+ggtitle(lv)+theme(legend.key.width =  unit(1, 'cm'))+xlab("")
}
ggarrange(plotlist = goL, ncol=2, nrow=3,common.legend = T)
